In R 4.0.3 on Windows, which uses internal tzcode, using as.POSIXlt(., origin = "1970-1-1") , yes, always GMT BST.

However,

Sys.setenv(TZ="Europe/London")
for (i in 1:10)
print(attr(as.POSIXlt(.POSIXct(as.numeric(1:10))), 'tzone'))

also gives GMT BST for the first and BST BST for subsequent invocations.

The same result is obtained by first defining

origin <- as.POSIXct("1970-1-1", tz = "UTC")

and using as.POSIXlt(., origin = origin) .

